🔹 LifecycleEvent kya hai?
LifecycleEvent SailPoint me Identity ke lifecycle me hone wale changes ko represent karta hai.
Jab identity create, update, disable, delete hoti hai → ek LifecycleEvent generate hota hai,
Ye events Identity Governance ke liye track aur trigger hote hain.

🔹 LifeCycleEvent ka kaam:-
()Track Identity Changes:
Kaun sa identity ka kya change hua
Example: email change, role assign, manager change.

()Trigger Policies / Rules:
Approval workflow trigger karna
Notifications bhejna.

()Audit & Reporting:
Historical changes record rakhna
Compliance / audit ke liye use.

🔹 LifecycleEvent ke Types (Common):-
Event Type	           Kya hota hai
CREATE	          Nayi identity create hui
MODIFY/UPDATE	  Existing identity me change hua
DISABLE	          Identity temporarily disable hui
DELETE	          Identity delete hui
ENABLE	          Identity re-enable hui.

✅ Full Methods:-
getType()
setType(LifecycleEventType type)
getIdentity()
setIdentity(Identity identity)
getTimestamp()
setTimestamp(Date timestamp)
getAttributes()
setAttributes(Map<String, Object> attributes)
getPreviousValues()
setPreviousValues(Map<String, Object> previousValues)
getNewValues()
setNewValues(Map<String, Object> newValues)
getEventId()
setEventId(String eventId)
clone()
equals(Object obj)
hashCode()
toString()
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1️⃣ getType() & setType(LifecycleEventType type):-
Kaam: Event ka type set aur get karne ke liye (CREATE, UPDATE, DELETE, etc.)
LifecycleEvent event = new LifecycleEvent();
event.setType(LifecycleEventType.CREATE);
System.out.println(event.getType());
Output:-
CREATE

2️⃣ getIdentity() & setIdentity(Identity identity):-
Kaam: Kaun si identity pe event hua usko set/get karne ke liye
Identity user = new Identity("Kishan");
event.setIdentity(user);
System.out.println(event.getIdentity().getName());
Output:-
Kishan

3️⃣ getTimestamp() & setTimestamp(Date timestamp):-
Kaam: Event kab hua uska timestamp set/get karna
Date now = new Date();
event.setTimestamp(now);
System.out.println(event.getTimestamp());
Output:-
Tue Mar 21 11:45:30 IST 2026

4️⃣ getAttributes() & setAttributes(Map<String, Object> attributes):-
Kaam: Event ke saath associated attributes store karna
Map<String, Object> attrs = new HashMap<>();
attrs.put("email", "kishan@example.com");
event.setAttributes(attrs);
System.out.println(event.getAttributes());
Output:-
{email=kishan@example.com}

4️⃣ getAttributes() & setAttributes(Map<String, Object> attributes):-
Kaam: Event ke saath associated attributes store karna
Map<String, Object> attrs = new HashMap<>();
attrs.put("email", "kishan@example.com");
event.setAttributes(attrs);
System.out.println(event.getAttributes());
Output:-
{email=kishan@example.com}

5️⃣ getPreviousValues() & setPreviousValues(Map<String, Object> previousValues):-
Kaam: Event se pehle identity ke purane values
Map<String, Object> prev = new HashMap<>();
prev.put("email", "old@example.com");
event.setPreviousValues(prev);
System.out.println(event.getPreviousValues());
Output:-
{email=old@example.com}

6️⃣ getNewValues() & setNewValues(Map<String, Object> newValues):-
Kaam: Event ke baad identity ke naye values
Map<String, Object> newVal = new HashMap<>();
newVal.put("email", "kishan@example.com");
event.setNewValues(newVal);
System.out.println(event.getNewValues());
Output:-
{email=kishan@example.com}

7️⃣ getEventId() & setEventId(String eventId):-
Kaam: Event ka unique ID set/get karne ke liye
event.setEventId("EVT12345");
System.out.println(event.getEventId());
Output:-
EVT12345

8️⃣ clone():-
Kaam: Event ka duplicate create karta hai
LifecycleEvent copy = event.clone();
System.out.println(copy.getEventId());
Output:-
EVT12345

9️⃣ equals(Object obj):-
Kaam: Do events same hai ya nahi check karta hai
LifecycleEvent e2 = event.clone();
System.out.println(event.equals(e2));
Output:-
true

10️⃣ hashCode():-
Kaam: Event ka unique hash code generate karta hai
System.out.println(event.hashCode());
Output (example):-
12345678

11️⃣ toString():-
Kaam: Event ka readable representation return karta hai
System.out.println(event.toString());
Output (example):-
LifecycleEvent[eventId=EVT12345, type=CREATE, identity=Kishan, timestamp=Tue Mar 21 11:45:30 IST 2026]
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
